// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/XXSyD3 bounding sphere binary tree test performance, 2024 by jt
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/l3jczt bounding sphere binary tree
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/XXByzt bounding sphere pair

// Performance test: ray-marching 32 grid-spheres in a tree structure of nested bounding spheres.
// Unfortunately turns out to be slower than I had hoped - perhaps because spheres are paired randomly
// (which results in too much overlap of bounding spheres).

// But still faster than naive "render-all" approach - compare:
// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/43BcD3 32 naive gridspheres groundtruth

// tags: bounding, volume, sphere, raymarch, intersect, tree, bvh, hierarchy, performance, test

